= [http://www.nadadventist.org/ www.nadadventist.org]\n|remarks =\n}}\n{{Seventh-day Adventism}}\nThe '''[[Seventh-day Adventist Church]]''' runs a large [[Seventh-day Adventist education|educational system]] throughout the world. As of 2008, 1678<ref name=\"Statistics\">[http://www.adventist.org/world_church/facts_and_figures/index.html.en Seventh-day Adventist Statistics] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090529072357/http://www.adventist.org/world_church/facts_and_figures/index.html.en |date=2009-05-29 }}. Office of Statistics & Archives. Retrieved 2009-08-05</ref> '''[[secondary school]]s''' are affiliated with the Church. Some schools offer both elementary and secondary education.\nThey are a part of the [[Seventh-day Adventist education|Seventh-day Adventist education system]], the world's second largest Christian school system.<ref>http://www.csmonitor.com/Commentary/Opinion/2010/1115/For-real-education-reform-take-a-cue-from-the-Adventists\"the second largest Christian school system in the world has been steadily outperforming the national average&nbsp;\u2013 across all demographics.\"</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.religionfacts.com/christianity/denominations/seventh_day_adventist.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-03-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150323223151/http://www.religionfacts.com/christianity/denominations/seventh_day_adventist.htm |archivedate=2015-03-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|title=Department of Education, Seventh-day Adventist Church\n|url=http://education.gc.adventist.org/about.html\n|accessdate=2010-06-18\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://news.adventist.org/2003/04/worl-church-a-closer-look-at-higher-eucatio.html \n |title=World Church: A Closer Look at Higher Education \n |first=Wendi \n |last=Rogers \n |first2=Mark A. \n |last2=Kellner \n |date=April 1, 2003 \n |publisher=[[Adventist News Network]] \n |accessdate=2010-06-19 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724224535/http://news.adventist.org/2003/04/worl-church-a-closer-look-at-higher-eucatio.html \n |archivedate=July 24, 2011 \n}}</ref>\n\n==[[Southern Africa-Indian Ocean Division of Seventh-day Adventists|Southern Africa and Indian Ocean Division]]==\n\n===Botswana===\n* Eastern Gate Academy, Francistown\n* Emmanuel Adventist Academy, Molepolole\n* Mogoditshane Adventist Primary, Mogoditshane\n* Mountain View Adventist Academy, Mogoditshane\n\n===South Africa===\n* Aurum Seventh-Day Adventist Academy\n* Bethel high School\n* Blue Hills College\n* Cancele Senior Secondary School\n* Good Hope High School\n* Good Hope Primary School\n* Grahamstown Adventist School\n* Helderberg Pre-primary, Primary, High School and University\n* Hillcrest Primary School\n* Keitsleigh Primary School\n* Paterson Park\n* Presda \n* Riverside Primary School\n* Sedaven Primary and High School\n* West Rand Sda Primary School\n\n===Zambia===\n* Mupapa Secondary School\n* Rusangu Secondary School\n*King' s Highway primary and secondary school\n*Rusangu University\n\n===Zimbabwe===\n* Anderson Adventist High School, [[Gweru]]\n* Anderson Adventist Primary School, [[Gweru]]\n* Anderson Mutiweshiri Secondary, Mutiweshiri, Wedza\n* Bemhiwa Primary School, Bocha\n* Bulawayo Adventist Secondary School, [[Bulawayo]]\n* Chikwariro Adventist High, Bocha\n* Chinembiri Secondary\n* Fairview Primary School, Bulawayo\n* Gunde Primary and High School, Gweru\n* Handina Adventist Primary and Secondary School, Nyazura\n* Hanke Mission Primary and Secondary School, [[Shurugwi]]\n* Karirwi Adventist Mission, Bocha\n* Katsenga Secondary\n* Lower Gwelo Primary, Secondary and High School, [[Lower Gwelo]]\n* Lowveld Adventist Primary School, Chiredzi\n* Mandora SDA Primary School, Mhondoro/Kadoma\n* Maranatha Adventist High, Primary School, Bulawayo\n* Marewo Primary School, Bocha\n* Mauya Secondary School\n* Mkhosana Adventist Secondary School, Victoria Falls\n* Mtanki SDA Primary School, Gokwe\n* Muk